Package machinery

Class Tractor

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.image.ImageView
machinery.Vehicle
machinery.Tractor
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class Tractor extends Vehicle
This class models the tractor vehicle. Particularly it updates the images of the tractor according to the direction it is driving to, as well as checking if there are arablefields nearby it can interact with using its equipment.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Tom Zehle

  • Constructor Details

    • Tractor

      public Tractor​(int x, int y, int maxfuel, double speed, CollisionChecker bc, AvailableObjectsNearby aonb, GameState gs)
      The constructor for the tractor class. Calls the super constructor of vehicle. Sets the image to facing to the left and sets the variable save.
      Parameters:
      int - x the x coordinate of the tractor.
      int - y the y coordinate of the tractor.
      AvailableObjectsNearby - aonb the instance of AONB, allowing to search for nearby objects.
      GameState - gs the instance of the game state, only used to pass it to the super constructor.

  • Method Details

    • checkmovementactions

      public void checkmovementactions()
      Checks if there are actions to be made if a movement is detected. If a field is nearby and a cultivator is attached: cultivate that field! If a field is nearby and a seeddrill is attached: sow that field!

    • getTrailer

      public Equipment getTrailer()
      getter for the trailer
      Returns:
      Trailer trailer

    • equip

      public void equip​(Equipment equipment)
      Equips a equipment if there's no trailer attached yet by setting the trailer variable to the passed equipment parameter. Deequip if there is already a trailer attached.
      Parameters:
      Equipment - equipment the equipment supposed to be equipped.

    • deequip

      public void deequip()
      Deequips the trailer by setting the trailer variable to null.

    • moveup

      public void moveup()
      sets the image to face up and updates the coordinates of the tractor. Calls checkmovementactions. If a trailer is attached, its image as well as its coordinates are updated accordingly. Checks for collisions.

    • moveright

      public void moveright()
      sets the image to face to the right and updates the coordinates of the tractor. Calls checkmovementactions. If a trailer is attached, its image as well as its coordinates are updated accordingly. Checks for collisions.

    • movedown

      public void movedown()
      sets the image to face down and updates the coordinates of the tractor. Calls checkmovementactions. If a trailer is attached, its image as well as its coordinates are updated accordingly. Checks for collisions.

    • moveleft

      public void moveleft()
      sets the image to face to the left and updates the coordinates of the tractor. Calls checkmovementactions. If a trailer is attached, its image as well as its coordinates are updated accordingly. Checks for collisions.

    • getFuel
